me.timothy.tests.database

Class LoanMappingTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.timothy.tests.database.LoanMappingTest
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MysqlLoanMappingTest

    public class LoanMappingTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes a test focused on a LoanMapping in a MappingDatabase. The database must be completely empty after each setUp. The database will be modified after each run - do not run against real databases.

        public void testTest()

      • testSave

        public void testSave()
        Tests that simple Loan saving can be done without error by verifying that, after saving:
        • the Loan.id is strictly positive
        • when all Loans are fetched, only the Loans that have been saved are returned, using an equality check.

      • testFetchLendersIdsWithNewLoanSince

        public void testFetchLendersIdsWithNewLoanSince()
        Tests LoanMapping#fetchLenderIdsWithNewLoanSince(Timestamp).
        • Only returns user ids that have a Loan created at as lender after the Timestamp that is sent to it.
        • Does not duplicate user ids.

      • testFetchWithBorrowerAndOrLender

        public void testFetchWithBorrowerAndOrLender()
        Tests LoanMapping#fetchWithBorrowerAndOrLender(int, int, boolean) (from here on, just the test function)
        • When the strict tag is set to false, the test function returns loans in which the lender or the borrower matches the respective lenderId or borrowerId.
        • When the strict tag is set to true, the test function returns loans that match both the Loan.lenderId and Loan.borrowerId.
        • Regardless of the strict tag, the test function ignores deleted loans

      • testFetchNumberOfLoansWithUserAsLender

        public void testFetchNumberOfLoansWithUserAsLender()
        Tests LoanMapping.fetchNumberOfLoansWithUserAsLender(int)
        • Should only return the count of loans as lender
        • Should not count deleted loans.

      • testFetchDeleted

        public void testFetchDeleted()
        This contains further tests to verify the LoanMapping handles deleted loans appropriately.
        • fetchAll() should return deleted loans
        • fetchWithBorrowerAndOrLender(int, int, boolean) should not return deleted loans
        • fetchNumberOfLoansWithUserAsLender(int) should not return deleted loans
        • fetchLenderIdsWithNewLoanSince(Timestamp) should not return deleted loans
